# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# This .gitignore is configured to:
# 1. Keep all code and scripts (src/)
# 2. Keep documentation (README files)
# 3. Keep small configuration files
# 4. Keep .gitkeep files for directory structure
# 5. Exclude all large data files (BAM, FASTQ, reference genomes)
# 6. Exclude all generated outputs (results/)
# 7. Keep SEG files (relatively small, scientifically important)
# 8. Exclude all temporary and cache files
#
# To track specific files that are ignored, use:
#   git add -f filename
# =============================================================================
